<div class="bibEntry"><p class="bib">423. Cheskin, Louis. Color Guide for Marketing Media. New York: Macmillan, 1954. 209 pp. Index, color illus. </p><p class="annot">Effective color use in packaging, advertising, and other marketing media is explained in this important early work on the subject. Topics include: the physical, chemical, physiological, and psychological aspects of color; the impact of color on visibility and legibility; and the power of color as revealed in color symbolism and preference. Anyone interested in color and marketing will want to be familiar with this clearly written basic work. </p></div>
